The title compound was prepared using the procedure described in Example 93 replacing 2-pyridin-3-ylethanamine with 2-morpholin-4-yl-2-pyridin-3-ylethylamine.
1H NMR (DMSO, 400MHz) δ 12.40 (1H, s), 9.14 (1H, m), 9.05 (1H, d, J=4.0 Hz), 8.68 (1H, s), 8.60-8.50 (2H, m), 8.00 (1H, m), 7.72 (1H, dd, J=4.2 and 8.4Hz), 7.55-7.40 (4H, m), 4.63 (1H, dd, J=15.4 and 6.8 Hz), 4.53 (1H, dd, J=15.4 and 5.7 Hz), 4.00-3.00 (8H, m) ppm.
